1
00:01:04,719 --> 00:01:06,599
This is so pretty! How much?

2
00:01:06,879 --> 00:01:07,760
Fourteen each.

3
00:01:07,920 --> 00:01:09,200
Sister, it's a great deal.

4
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,120
I'll take two then.

5
00:01:10,319 --> 00:01:11,280
Two for twenty-eight.

6
00:01:11,519 --> 00:01:12,519
Thank you, pretty sister!

7
00:01:12,680 --> 00:01:13,400
Bye, little one.

8
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:14,359
Bye-bye.

9
00:01:18,319 --> 00:01:20,760
Little boss, I'd like to buy a small conch.

10
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,799
How much for a small conch, sister Tang Yi?

11
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,439
Slow down, slow down.

12
00:01:26,439 --> 00:01:27,200
Sister Tang Yi.

13
00:01:27,319 --> 00:01:29,040
I feel like someone else is here.

14
00:01:29,239 --> 00:01:31,000
Did you bring your boyfriend over, sister?

15
00:01:35,359 --> 00:01:36,200
Don't talk nonsense.

16
00:01:36,519 --> 00:01:38,840
This is sister's new colleague, Dr. Jiang.

17
00:01:39,079 --> 00:01:41,319
Brother, can I touch your face?

18
00:01:45,719 --> 00:01:46,280
Sure.

19
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:13,360
Mengmeng

20
00:02:14,599 --> 00:02:14,960
Mengmeng

21
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,800
Mengmeng

22
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:24,800
Mengmeng

23
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,039
Daddy's here

24
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:27,120
Daddy's here

25
00:02:27,319 --> 00:02:28,479
Don't be afraid, don't be afraid

26
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,080
Someone, please help me

27
00:02:30,280 --> 00:02:31,680
Save my child

28
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,919
Won't someone help me? Mengmeng

29
00:02:35,080 --> 00:02:36,319
How did the child fall so badly?

30
00:02:37,520 --> 00:02:38,240
Make way!

31
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:42,000
She's lost a tooth too

32
00:02:42,039 --> 00:02:42,719
Don't touch her

33
00:02:45,879 --> 00:02:46,560
You're a doctor?

34
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:57,680
Quick, call 911

35
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,439
Brother, you're so handsome

36
00:03:06,719 --> 00:03:08,240
You've got such great taste

37
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:14,800
But these hands feel so familiar

38
00:03:14,919 --> 00:03:17,439
Brother, haven't we met somewhere?

39
00:03:17,599 --> 00:03:20,199
I feel like we've met before too

40
00:03:20,479 --> 00:03:21,960
So young and already learning to chat up boys

41
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:24,240
Careful, you'll scare Brother off

42
00:03:24,719 --> 00:03:26,479
Then I'll give him a small conch

43
00:03:28,479 --> 00:03:31,080
Already Winning hearts at such a young age

44
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,080
What'll you be like when you grow up?

45
00:03:34,319 --> 00:03:34,879
Oh, right

46
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,960
Sister brought you a little gift today

47
00:03:37,319 --> 00:03:38,199
Hold out your hand

48
00:03:40,599 --> 00:03:41,360
Feel it

49
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,759
This is my baby tooth

50
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:47,240
So clever

51
00:03:47,719 --> 00:03:49,520
Sister filled all the little black holes

52
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:50,599
on your baby tooth.

53
00:03:51,159 --> 00:03:51,800
From now on

54
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:54,280
cut down on chocolate and candy

55
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:56,080
Never drink soda like it's water

56
00:03:56,199 --> 00:03:56,879
Did you hear me?

57
00:03:59,759 --> 00:04:01,000
How many did you sell today?

58
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,280
Just a few

59
00:04:02,439 --> 00:04:03,639
Only a few?

60
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:04,520
It's okay

61
00:04:04,759 --> 00:04:06,240
I'll have Brother Jiang help you later

62
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,759
Buy everything up, how's that?

63
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:11,319
So how about a thank-you? A hug?

64
00:04:15,479 --> 00:04:16,399
My turn now

65
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:21,279
Come, give sister a hug

66
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:43,959
Mom

67
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,040
Your daughter will definitely succeed

68
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,040
Right?

69
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,560
Thank you.

70
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:26,959
Dr. Jiang.

71
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:34,879
Dr. Jiang.

72
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,399
Ever tried a Ginger Sugar Latte?

73
00:05:37,639 --> 00:05:38,279
No.

74
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:41,160
Dr. Tang, good morning.

75
00:05:42,399 --> 00:05:44,000
Nice lipstick shade today.

76
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:48,959
Something's off with him.

77
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:50,199
He's in love.

78
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,079
Hey, that's not right, young man.

79
00:05:58,879 --> 00:06:00,600
This back tooth of mine,

80
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:03,120
Why don't you implant it today too?

81
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:05,199
Your diabetes isn't well controlled.

82
00:06:05,360 --> 00:06:06,240
Your blood sugar is unstable.

83
00:06:06,319 --> 00:06:07,959
Wound healing will be poor.

84
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:10,519
The dental implant could get infected repeatedly.

85
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,720
That's right, Granny.

86
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:13,120
The teeth you have remaining

87
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,199
can still do their job.

88
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:16,079
They basically meet your daily needs.

89
00:06:16,319 --> 00:06:17,439
Once your blood sugar stabilizes,

90
00:06:17,639 --> 00:06:19,279
we'll reassess if a dental implant is suitable.

91
00:06:19,399 --> 00:06:20,560
Alright, alright.

92
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:22,120
Whatever you say.

93
00:06:22,759 --> 00:06:23,720
Silly boy.

94
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:25,600
Turning down good money.

95
00:06:42,639 --> 00:06:43,319
You're welcome

96
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,279
It's hideous!

97
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:22,360
Compensate.

98
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,120
Compensate.

99
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:28,639
Please, have a seat.

100
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:33,399
My name is Ge Baogen.

101
00:07:33,839 --> 00:07:35,000
I'm 63 years old.

102
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:36,360
On July 17th,

103
00:07:37,079 --> 00:07:38,079
at your hospital,

104
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,319
a Dr. Qin

105
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,759
fitted me with a Denture.

106
00:07:41,079 --> 00:07:42,319
I paid over 5,000 yuan.

107
00:07:42,839 --> 00:07:44,000
After only a few days,

108
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:45,800
it broke.

109
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,199
Isn't your hospital ripping people off?

110
00:07:49,959 --> 00:07:51,199
The Dr. Qin you're talking about,

111
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:53,040
which Dr. Qin is it?

112
00:07:53,839 --> 00:07:54,759
It's that one,

113
00:07:55,959 --> 00:07:57,839
Qin, that Dr. Qin.

114
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:01,959
The Dr. Qin you mentioned

115
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,120
has already retired.

116
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:05,839
As for your Denture,

117
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,399
it's just normal wear and tear.

118
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,279
We can't compensate you.

119
00:08:08,759 --> 00:08:09,839
Can't compensate?

120
00:08:10,519 --> 00:08:11,720
July 17th,

121
00:08:11,879 --> 00:08:13,160
10:30 in the morning,

122
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,160
at your hospital,

123
00:08:14,199 --> 00:08:15,600
that Dr. Qin

124
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:17,279
fitted me with a Denture.

125
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,600
My grandson told me, after I got it in,

126
00:08:19,839 --> 00:08:21,399
to take him out to buy candy.

127
00:08:22,319 --> 00:08:24,160
Does your hospital listen to reason at all?

128
00:08:24,319 --> 00:08:25,199
Please, calm down.

129
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,879
Here, have a seat first.

130
00:08:27,199 --> 00:08:28,040
Let's talk it through.

131
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:29,160
Here.

132
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,240
Well, we can't compensate you,

133
00:08:31,439 --> 00:08:32,480
but we can repair it for you.

134
00:08:32,639 --> 00:08:32,879
Re...

135
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,480
Repair? Why should I get it repaired?

136
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:35,759
I don't want it repaired.

137
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,279
Sir, listen to me.

138
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,200
Compensate!

139
00:08:41,519 --> 00:08:43,200
Give me back my grandson!

140
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:43,919
Sir!

141
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,399
Give me back my grandson! Sir!

142
00:08:45,519 --> 00:08:46,840
Mr. Ge! Mr. Ge!

143
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:48,519
Mr. Ge, please calm down.

144
00:08:48,879 --> 00:08:50,759
Unbelievable. You came here again.

145
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:55,639
Auntie Jiang, we found him.

146
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:56,759
He's over here.

147
00:08:57,519 --> 00:08:58,159
Coming.

148
00:08:58,759 --> 00:09:00,120
Mr. Ge, are you hurt?

149
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:00,960
Take a good look.

150
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,440
I'm the victim here.

151
00:09:03,879 --> 00:09:04,320
Ridiculous.

152
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,799
You damn old fool.

153
00:09:06,039 --> 00:09:07,879
Turn my back for a second, and you cause trouble.

154
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,000
What did this doctor ever do to you?

155
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,519
Splashing her like that?

156
00:09:11,519 --> 00:09:12,120
He...

157
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:13,559
He won't compensate me.

158
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,080
Compensate for what?

159
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:18,080
You've used those teeth for ten years.

160
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,919
Why on earth should she compensate you?

161
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,159
It's fine, Auntie Jiang.

162
00:09:21,399 --> 00:09:22,000
Calm down.

163
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,039
Just calm down.

164
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:24,919
Are you all right?

165
00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:28,960
I'm so sorry, Doctor.

166
00:09:29,759 --> 00:09:31,159
This old man of mine...

167
00:09:31,399 --> 00:09:32,759
He has dementia.

168
00:09:33,159 --> 00:09:34,360
He gets confused sometimes.

169
00:09:34,559 --> 00:09:36,960
Yells at anyone he sees.

170
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,399
I'm really sorry.

171
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:40,080
We caused you trouble. So sorry.

172
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,120
It's okay, Auntie.

173
00:09:41,279 --> 00:09:42,679
It's fine. Come on.

174
00:09:43,559 --> 00:09:44,559
My grandson.

175
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:46,480
Why are you crying?

176
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:47,919
Don't cry.

177
00:09:49,159 --> 00:09:50,600
Look what Grandpa got you.

178
00:09:51,279 --> 00:09:52,399
A lollipop.

179
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,240
Cola-flavored.

180
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:55,720
It's your favorite, isn't it?

181
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:56,799
Have a taste.

182
00:09:57,039 --> 00:09:59,200
Open your eyes and look properly.

183
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:01,399
I'm your wife.

184
00:10:03,279 --> 00:10:05,519
Come on, let's go home.

185
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:07,480
I'm sorry.

186
00:10:07,799 --> 00:10:08,759
- We're leaving. - It's fine, Auntie.

187
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:09,360
Take it slow.

188
00:10:09,480 --> 00:10:10,200
Let's go.

189
00:10:10,519 --> 00:10:12,720
Where's my grandson?

190
00:10:13,159 --> 00:10:14,159
I don't see him.

191
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,159
He went home.

192
00:10:15,279 --> 00:10:17,279
I still need to buy him candy. All right, all right.

193
00:10:25,279 --> 00:10:26,639
Mr. Ge's grandson...

194
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,559
went missing on July 17th, ten years ago.

195
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,039
When he's lucid,

196
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:31,919
all these years,

197
00:10:32,080 --> 00:10:33,200
he searches the surrounding streets,

198
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:35,320
back and forth, over and over.

199
00:10:35,759 --> 00:10:36,919
When he's confused,

200
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:38,279
like today,

201
00:10:38,559 --> 00:10:39,600
he mixes things up.

202
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,919
No one can control his emotions.

203
00:10:44,879 --> 00:10:45,879
Does he come here often?

204
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,200
His grandson is gone.

205
00:10:50,679 --> 00:10:51,960
His daughter-in-law left.

206
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:53,159
He fell out with his son too.

207
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,279
The son's been gone ten years, never returned.

208
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:58,279
Where else can he go?

209
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,080
Only here

210
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:02,240
can we sit and chat with him,

211
00:11:02,799 --> 00:11:03,559
keep him company.

212
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,399
You burned your hand.

213
00:11:14,399 --> 00:11:15,279
I'm not that delicate.

214
00:11:16,679 --> 00:11:17,440
Didn't the nurse tell you?

215
00:11:17,519 --> 00:11:18,840
There's a first aid kit in the office.

216
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:29,799
Lift your hand.

217
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,519
So beautiful.

218
00:12:29,879 --> 00:12:30,679
Danio.

219
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:35,559
Looks like

220
00:12:35,919 --> 00:12:37,080
I came at a bad time.

221
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:11,639
If you have bad teeth,

222
00:13:11,720 --> 00:13:13,000
will getting a Denture or a dental implant

223
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,200
solve the problem once and for all?

224
00:13:14,559 --> 00:13:15,279
Of course not.

225
00:13:15,759 --> 00:13:17,759
Even the best Denture needs regular upkeep.

226
00:13:18,240 --> 00:13:19,639
It's recommended that every six months to a year,

227
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:21,360
you visit the hospital for routine checkups,

228
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,080
to ensure the Denture

229
00:13:22,240 --> 00:13:23,759
or crowns remain securely in place.

230
00:13:24,039 --> 00:13:26,679
If needed, adjust or replace them promptly.
